     You outdid yourself this time.  As a mental health professional, you of all people should know that you should not project difficulties, know matter how extreme, with one person of a group to another. Also at your age, you could be expected to be the more mature of the two of you. I'm sorry about your lawsuit, but people in this country do sue too much. I read that the DC metro area has more lawyers than half of Japan. I also know of a family where a son-in-law tried to sue his mother-in-law over a loose porch step. As for how Lien's family &quot;earns&quot; its bread and butter; neither you nor I nor anyone on this site knows the facts from Shinola, nor is it any of our business. Catharsis is one thing, your unrestrained &quot;flame&quot; was another. Besides, you can't stir a pot very well if you burn all the contents.<br>

